('fsOUhzLv', 'SandBoxCore', 'Jalos'),
('fSPXXQCQ', 'SandBox', 'It''s a damn shame. I like duels - you don''t worry about arrows, or someone coming up from behind. No need to stay sober for hours on end waiting for a fight that never comes. Just a few minutes of trouble, a bit of blood, and then usually a good meal afterwards.'),
('FSwVVdHV', 'SandBox', 'Still, men are willing to fight for me, though it gains them nothing, for no other reason that the throne is my right. I will not betray these men. If I win, in centuries to come, people will think back on my victory and think, ''Heavens smile on those who fight for their rights.'' That is all one can do.'),
